@@bNorthern Path, Scavenger Approach@@N~
@@bThe northern dune path narrows here as it descends from the ridge crest toward a broad natural hollow sheltered by two converging dune walls.@@N The shelter makes this area unusually quiet — wind passes overhead rather than through it — and the soft sand shows the layered imprint of previous camps. @@bFresh fire ash in a scraped pit, gnawed bone fragments, and the smell of rancid animal fat indicate recent occupation that was not caravan-related.@@N To the north, voices have been heard — not caravan calls, but the shorter, harder speech of people engaged in work rather than travel. The eastern descent from here is gradual, leading down toward the boundary zone.
